description: Least number such that number of divisors is n-th term from A014613 (numbers of form pqrs, products of exactly 4 primes, counted with multiplicity).
example: pqrs=210 is the 27th term in A014613; the smallest number with 210 divisors is 907200=2.2.2.2.2.2.3.3.3.3.5.5.7
author: _Labos Elemer_, Jun 06 2001
